    <string name="paste_example">Paste ByeDPI Example</string>
    <string name="dpi_config_guide"><b>DPI Bypass Guide:</b>\n\n• <b>Header + Split S1:</b> Good for simple SNI filtering.\n• <b>Disorder:</b> Effective against stateful DPI that expects strict ordering.\n• <b>SNI Split + OOB:</b> Best for aggressive blocking that inspects packet content deeply.\n• <b>Delay:</b> Increasing delay helps if the DPI uses reassembly timeouts.\n\n<b>Advanced Commands:</b>\n• <b>-s [N]:</b> Split at pos N. (+s for SNI relative)\n• <b>-q [N]:</b> Disorder at pos N.\n• <b>-o [N]:</b> OOB at pos N.\n• <b>-As/t/r:</b> Apply to SSL/TCP/Redirects.</string>

